  "articleSummary": "This technical retrospective details the author’s migration of an eight-year-old Gatsby blog to a modern static stack, arguing that Astro’s framework-agnostic design and rapid development workflow make it the optimal choice for performance-focused content sites. The author evaluates Remix and Next.js before settling on a stack centered on Astro, MDX, ShadcnUI, Tailwind CSS, Pagefind, Utterances, and Netlify, while highlighting Astro’s build-time rendering, content collections, and minimal client-side JavaScript output. Written in a practical, tutorial-style tone with a structured \"requirements-to-implementation\" framing, the piece targets front-end developers and static site users seeking to modernize legacy projects without vendor lock-in.",
